{"id":590744,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Niagara_Falls%2C_New_York","text":"Niagara Falls () is a city in Niagara County, New York, United States.\nAs of the 2010 census, the city had a total population of 50,193, down from the 55,593 recorded in the 2000 census.\nIt is across the Niagara River, across from the city of Niagara Falls, Ontario, and named after the famed Niagara Falls which they share. The city is within the Buffalo\u2013Niagara Falls Metropolitan Statistical Area as well as the Western New York region.","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"City","surface_form":"city","offset":22},{"uri":"Niagara_County%2C_New_York","surface_form":"Niagara County","offset":30},{"uri":"New_York_(state)","surface_form":"New York","offset":46},{"uri":"United_States","surface_form":"United States","offset":56},{"uri":"2010_United_States_Census","surface_form":"2010 census","offset":81},{"uri":"Population","surface_form":"population","offset":115},{"uri":"2000_United_States_Census","surface_form":"2000 census","offset":174},{"uri":"Niagara_River","surface_form":"Niagara River","offset":204},{"uri":"Niagara_Falls%2C_Ontario","surface_form":"Niagara Falls, Ontario","offset":243},{"uri":"Niagara_Falls","surface_form":"Niagara Falls","offset":293},{"uri":"Buffalo%E2%80%93Niagara_Falls_metropolitan_area","surface_form":"Buffalo\u2013Niagara Falls Metropolitan Statistical Area","offset":348},{"uri":"Western_New_York","surface_form":"Western New York","offset":415}]}